Former eNCA news anchor Shahan Ramkissoon has left the world of broadcasting for the corporate Public Relations industry. He announced the news on his social media platforms that he was joining Eclipse Communications as Chief Strategy Officer. “My new journey begins today I’m so excited,” he wrote. Shahan, presented NewsNight from 9pm-11pm and was known for holding politicians accountable, especially on allegations of corruption. The 36-year-old worked for the channel for 12 years and has been described as the voice of South Africans.   Also Read: eNCA prime-time news anchor Shahan Ramkissoon is leaving For the latest entertainment news from Sunday World, click here. Or read the latest from Shwashwi here. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here.